      • graphPattern

        protected com.bigdata.rdf.sail.sparql.GroupGraphPattern graphPattern
        Used to manage collection and nesting of graph patterns. This is mostly handled by GroupGraphPatternBuilder.

        Note: Both ASTExistsFunc and ASTNotExistsFunc have an inner graph pattern by they appear within value expressions.

      • visit

        public final FunctionNode visit(ASTIn node,
                 Object data)
                         throws VisitorException
        "IN" and "NOT IN" are infix notation operators. The syntax for "IN" is [NumericExpression IN ArgList]. However, the IN operators declared by the FunctionRegistry require that the outer NumericExpression is their first argument. The function registry optimizes several different cases, including where the set is empty, where it has one member, and where the members of the set are constants and the outer expression is a variable.
        Specified by:

        Overrides:

      • visit

        public final AssignmentNode visit(ASTGroupCondition node,
                   Object data)
                           throws VisitorException
        Aggregate value expressions in GROUP BY clause. The content of this production can be a VarNode, AssignmentNode, or FunctionNode (which handles both built-in functions and extension functions). However, we always wrap it as an AssignmentNode and return that. A VarNode will just bind itself. A bare FunctionNode will bind an anonymous variable.
